						<summary>

						<p>Same pillar, second face.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record the gift of land to the goddess Hōnkaradēvi by Jogadobbagaṇḍa Ballaya-Chōḍa of the Telugu-Chōḍa family, probably of land near the village of Nannūru as <hi rend="italic">Sarvanamasya</hi> for the up keep of the temple, in conformity with the tradition of this family of chiefs of the solar race in respect of the temples in Pākanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
